h3. Issue Summary

When the customer tries to enable the Jira <> Slack integration, in the manage apps menu, it throws an error in the UI:
{code}
Jira error: something went wrong while updating instance

Please try again later or contact support. Error ID: a0277e00-ae20-11e9-a990-ed7b9e555e0a
{code}


h3. Steps to Reproduce
 # Access the manage apps menu;
 # Navigate to Slack app;
 # Click on configure;
 # Toggle the _Enable Slack integration_ button;

h3. Expected Results

Slack integration should be enabled

h3. Actual Results

Error is shown in the UI

The below exception is thrown in the UI file:
{noformat}
Jira error: something went wrong while updating instance

Please try again later or contact support. Error ID: a0277e00-ae20-11e9-a990-ed7b9e555e0a
{noformat}
h3. Notes

h3. Workaround

 Currently there is no known workaround for this behavior.

According to the current implementation of [The new Pages feature in JIRA Software project|https://confluence.atlassian.com/cloudkb/the-new-pages-feature-in-jira-software-project-958770525.html], if you have Confluence and Jira linked by application link from the different Cloud instances, The page features from Jira doesn't work in a way to allow the user to connect to space from the Confluence instance. 

{quote}
h2. Connecting to a space
When you have Jira and Confluence on the same instance, you just need to connect a Jira project with a Confluence space, and you're good to go.{quote}

It would definitely help some of our customers by catering this scenario so that the page features can be used even the instances is connected from the application link.
